Automatic speech recognition (ASR) for conversational Austrian German is difficult, because (1) conversational
speech is structurally different from written language, and (2) models do not easily transfer to underrepresented varieties.
[1] The work is funded by grant P-32700-N from the Austrian Science Fund.

flowRoot.flowPara: Project goals [1]: how to design & train language models for automatic speech recognition (ASR) for conversational Austrian German, including components such as: prosody, conversation state.
